    "plainEnglish": "Shigellosis due to Shigella dysenteriae is a serious bacterial infection of the intestines caused by a germ called Shigella dysenteriae, which spreads through contaminated food or water or contact with infected people. This infection causes severe bloody diarrhea, abdominal cramps, fever, and dehydration, and is more dangerous than other types of shigellosis because this particular bacteria produces a toxin that can damage the intestines and kidneys. It's most common in areas with poor sanitation and is a major cause of diarrheal disease in developing countries.",
