    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, emergency medicine doctors, and gastroenterologists use this code when patients present with acute food poisoning symptoms in urgent care or emergency room settings. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients seeking treatment for acute foodborne illness, particularly when hospitalization or IV fluids are needed for severe cases.",
