    "plainEnglish": "This is a serious food poisoning caused by eating raw or undercooked seafood (especially oysters) contaminated with Vibrio vulnificus bacteria. The illness typically causes sudden severe stomach pain, vomiting, diarrhea, and sometimes fever; in severe cases, especially in people with weak immune systems or liver disease, the infection can spread to the bloodstream and cause life-threatening complications including sepsis and skin infections.",
