    "code": "A06.81",
    "rawCode": "A0681",
    "shortDesc": "Amebic cystitis",
    "longDesc": "Amebic cystitis",
    "plainEnglish": "Amebic cystitis is a bladder infection caused by a parasite called Entamoeba histolytica, which is spread through contaminated water or food. This parasite invades the bladder lining, causing inflammation, pain during urination, frequent urges to urinate, and sometimes bloody urine. It's rare in developed countries but more common in tropical and subtropical regions where sanitation is poor.",
    "whoUses": "Infectious disease specialists, urologists, and emergency medicine physicians diagnose and treat amebic cystitis, typically in patients with a history of travel to endemic areas or exposure to contaminated water. This code appears on patient EOBs when treating parasitic infections in outpatient or hospitalized settings, though it is relatively uncommon in U.S. medical billing.",
