    "rawCode": "A0682",
    "shortDesc": "Other amebic genitourinary infections",
    "longDesc": "Other amebic genitourinary infections",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a parasitic infection caused by amebas (tiny single-celled organisms) that affects the genitourinary system—the organs involved in reproduction and urination. Amebic infections typically occur after drinking contaminated water or eating contaminated food in areas with poor sanitation, and the parasite can travel through the bloodstream to infect the bladder, urethra, or reproductive organs. Patients may experience painful urination, abnormal discharge, pelvic pain, or other urinary symptoms depending on which organs are affected.",
    "whoUses": "This code is primarily used by infectious disease specialists, urologists, and primary care physicians, typically in outpatient or office settings when diagnosing parasitic infections. It may also appear in emergency department records if a patient presents with acute genitourinary symptoms and travel history to endemic areas. This code is not commonly seen on standard patient EOB statements unless the patient has already been diagnosed with amebiasis and is seeking specialized treatment.",
