    "plainEnglish": "Amebiasis is an infection caused by a parasite called Entamoeba histolytica, usually picked up by drinking contaminated water or eating contaminated food in tropical areas. The parasite invades your intestines and can cause severe diarrhea, abdominal cramps, and bloody stools; in some cases, it can spread to the liver or other organs and cause serious complications. This code indicates amebiasis when doctors haven't specified exactly where in your body the infection is located or what type of symptoms you're experiencing.",
