    "plainEnglish": "Cyclosporiasis is a parasitic infection of the intestines caused by eating contaminated food or water containing a microscopic parasite called Cyclospora. Most commonly linked to fresh produce like lettuce, berries, and herbs, this infection causes watery diarrhea, stomach cramps, nausea, and fatigue that can last for weeks if untreated. The symptoms typically start 7–10 days after exposure and can range from mild to severe, depending on how much of the parasite you ingested.",
