    "longDesc": "Tuberculosis of larynx, trachea and bronchus",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means that tuberculosis (a serious bacterial infection caused by Mycobacterium tuberculosis) has spread to the voice box, windpipe, and/or airways in the lungs. A person with this condition might experience a persistent hoarse voice, difficulty swallowing, chronic cough, and chest pain—especially because the infection is damaging the tissues that control breathing and speech. This is a form of \"pulmonary tuberculosis\" that affects the upper respiratory tract rather than just the lung tissue itself.",
