    "plainEnglish": "Tuberculous pleurisy is an infection of the thin membrane surrounding the lungs (called the pleura) caused by the tuberculosis bacteria. This condition causes fluid to build up between the lung lining and chest wall, leading to chest pain that worsens with breathing, shortness of breath, and a persistent cough. It typically develops when TB bacteria spread from the lungs to this protective membrane, and patients may experience fever and fatigue as the infection progresses.",
