    "shortDesc": "Tuberculosis of spine",
    "longDesc": "Tuberculosis of spine",
    "plainEnglish": "Tuberculosis of the spine (also called Pott's disease) is a serious bone infection caused by the tuberculosis bacteria spreading to the vertebrae in the backbone. This typically develops when someone has untreated or poorly controlled tuberculosis in their lungs, and the infection gradually spreads through the bloodstream to the spine. Patients may experience back pain, spinal deformity, weakness in the legs, or loss of feeling, and if untreated, can develop permanent paralysis or severe spine curvature.",
