    "plainEnglish": "Tuberculosis of the cervix means a tuberculosis infection has spread to the cervix, which is the lower part of the uterus that connects to the vagina. This is a form of extrapulmonary tuberculosis (TB outside the lungs) caused by the bacterium Mycobacterium tuberculosis. Symptoms may include abnormal vaginal bleeding or discharge, pelvic pain, and difficulty with menstrual cycles, though some women may have no obvious symptoms and the infection is only discovered during testing or examination.",
