    "longDesc": "Tuberculous peritonitis",
    "plainEnglish": "Tuberculous peritonitis is a serious infection of the membrane that lines the inside of your abdomen and covers most of your abdominal organs. This occurs when tuberculosis (TB), the same bacteria that usually infects the lungs, spreads to this abdominal lining and causes inflammation, fluid buildup, and pain. Patients typically experience severe abdominal pain, swelling, fever, and weight loss, and the condition develops when TB bacteria from elsewhere in the body (often the lungs or lymph nodes) spread to the abdomen.",
