    "plainEnglish": "Tuberculosis of the adrenal glands is a serious infection caused by the tuberculosis bacterium that has spread from the lungs to attack the small hormone-producing glands that sit on top of your kidneys. This is a rare but dangerous form of TB that can damage these glands and interfere with important hormone production, potentially causing symptoms like weakness, fatigue, low blood pressure, and loss of appetite. It usually develops in people who have untreated or poorly controlled tuberculosis elsewhere in their body.",
