    "plainEnglish": "Tuberculosis of the spleen is a serious infection caused by the tuberculosis bacterium that has spread to the spleen, a fist-sized organ that filters blood and helps fight infections. This typically occurs when someone has active tuberculosis in their lungs or other parts of the body, and the infection spreads through the bloodstream to the spleen. Patients may experience abdominal pain, an enlarged spleen that can be felt below the rib cage, fever, weight loss, and general fatigue.",
