    "plainEnglish": "Anthrax is a serious infectious disease caused by bacteria called Bacillus anthracis, which can be transmitted through contact with infected animals or contaminated animal products like hides, wool, or meat. The infection can affect the skin (causing sores), lungs (causing severe respiratory illness), or digestive system depending on how the bacteria enters the body. Code A22.9 is used when a patient has confirmed anthrax but the specific type or affected body part hasn't been documented in detail.",
