    "plainEnglish": "Brucellosis is an infection caused by bacteria called Brucella melitensis, which people typically catch from infected animals or contaminated animal products like unpasteurized milk, cheese, or undercooked meat. The illness causes fever, sweats, fatigue, joint pain, and sometimes enlarged lymph nodes or organs, and symptoms can come and go over weeks or months if untreated. This infection is relatively rare in developed countries but more common in Mediterranean regions and the Middle East where infected goats and sheep are present.",
