    "whoUses": "Occupational medicine doctors, primary care physicians, and infectious disease specialists commonly diagnose and treat erysipeloid, particularly in emergency departments or urgent care settings when patients present with hand or finger infections. This code appears on EOB statements when patients seek treatment for work-related skin infections, especially in food handling, fishing, or butcher industries.",
