    "whoUses": "This code is used by primary care physicians, dermatologists, and occupational health providers when diagnosing skin infections in patients with occupational exposure to animal products or contaminated materials. It appears in office visits and urgent care settings, and may also be documented in ER visits; patients might see it on EOB statements if the infection required medical evaluation or antibiotic treatment.",
