    "plainEnglish": "Leptospirosis is a rare infectious disease caused by bacteria found in the urine of infected animals like rats, dogs, and cattle. This code refers to uncommon or atypical presentations of leptospirosis that don't fit into the more common forms (such as Weil's disease, which causes severe kidney and liver failure). Symptoms can range from flu-like illness with fever, muscle aches, and headaches to more serious complications depending on which organs are affected.",
