    "code": "A30.0",
    "rawCode": "A300",
    "shortDesc": "Indeterminate leprosy",
    "longDesc": "Indeterminate leprosy",
    "plainEnglish": "Indeterminate leprosy is the earliest stage of Hansen's disease, a chronic bacterial infection caused by Mycobacterium leprae that affects the skin and nerves. At this stage, doctors cannot yet classify the disease into a specific type because the infection is still developing and the immune response is unclear. Patients may notice a few pale or slightly reddened patches on the skin with mild or no loss of sensation, and the condition may progress to more definable forms of leprosy or resolve on its own.",
    "whoUses": "Infectious disease specialists, dermatologists, and tropical medicine experts use this code when diagnosing and managing early leprosy in endemic regions or in patients with recent exposure. This code appears in office visits, specialty consultations, and initial diagnostic workups, and may be documented on EOB statements for patients receiving treatment for Hansen's disease.",
