    "plainEnglish": "Borderline lepromatous leprosy is a moderately advanced form of Hansen's disease (leprosy), a chronic bacterial infection caused by Mycobacterium leprae. In this type, a person has numerous bacteria throughout their body and skin but hasn't yet progressed to the most severe lepromatous form. Patients typically experience widespread skin lesions, nerve damage, and possible deformities, though the immune system is still partially fighting the infection.",
