    "whoUses": "This code is used by infectious disease specialists, dermatologists, and primary care physicians, typically in outpatient clinic settings or during hospital consultations when evaluating a patient with suspected leprosy. It may appear on EOB statements for patients receiving care in endemic regions or at specialized centers treating neglected tropical diseases, though it is uncommon in routine U.S. healthcare billing.",
