    "whoUses": "Infectious disease specialists, internists, and emergency medicine physicians typically use this code when diagnosing atypical presentations of listeriosis during hospital admissions, ER evaluations, or consultations. This code may appear on patient EOB statements, particularly for those requiring hospitalization, IV antibiotics, or specialized testing; it is more commonly seen in immunocompromised patients, pregnant women, or the elderly who are at higher risk for severe infection.",
