    "plainEnglish": "Diphtheritic radiculomyelitis is a serious complication of diphtheria (a bacterial throat infection caused by Corynebacterium diphtheriae) where the bacteria produce toxins that damage the nerve roots and spinal cord. This causes inflammation and swelling of these nerve structures, leading to weakness, numbness, or paralysis—typically in the arms, legs, or muscles that control breathing. Patients may experience sudden weakness, tingling, or loss of movement weeks after the initial throat infection starts, and it can be life-threatening if the nerves controlling the diaphragm are affected.",
