    "plainEnglish": "This is a serious kidney infection caused by diphtheria toxin, a dangerous bacterial disease that damages the delicate filtering structures deep inside the kidneys (the tubules and spaces between the kidney's functional units). In diphtheria, a toxin produced by the bacteria spreads through the bloodstream and can poison the kidneys, leading to reduced kidney function, swelling, and sometimes kidney failure if left untreated. Patients may experience swollen legs and ankles, dark or foamy urine, and fatigue as their kidneys struggle to filter waste properly.",
