    "plainEnglish": "Whooping cough (pertussis) is a serious bacterial infection of the lungs and airways that causes severe, uncontrollable coughing fits—often ending with a distinctive high-pitched 'whooping' sound when the person tries to breathe in. This code indicates someone has whooping cough that has developed into pneumonia (infection and inflammation in the lung tissue itself), making it a more serious complication that can cause difficulty breathing, chest pain, and fatigue. The specific bacteria causing the whooping cough wasn't identified or recorded, but the pneumonia component means the lungs are now infected and inflamed beyond just the airways.",
