    "shortDesc": "Meningococcal carditis, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Meningococcal carditis, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Meningococcal carditis is a serious infection of the heart muscle and surrounding tissues caused by the meningococcus bacteria (Neisseria meningitidis). This condition develops when the bacteria spreads from the bloodstream to attack the heart, causing inflammation and potentially damaging the heart valves or the heart's ability to pump blood effectively. Patients may experience chest pain, shortness of breath, heart palpitations, and symptoms of shock or sepsis.",
    "whoUses": "This code is typically used by infectious disease specialists, cardiologists, and emergency medicine physicians in hospital settings, particularly in ICU or acute care environments when diagnosing and treating bacterial sepsis with cardiac involvement. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients hospitalized with meningococcal sepsis and requires inpatient treatment with antibiotics and cardiac monitoring.",
