    "code": "A39.53",
    "rawCode": "A3953",
    "shortDesc": "Meningococcal pericarditis",
    "longDesc": "Meningococcal pericarditis",
    "plainEnglish": "Meningococcal pericarditis is a serious infection where bacteria called Neisseria meningitidis (meningococcus) infect the sac surrounding the heart (pericardium), causing inflammation and fluid buildup. This condition typically develops as a complication of meningococcal disease and can cause chest pain, shortness of breath, and a characteristic friction rub sound when doctors listen to the heart. If untreated, the fluid accumulation can restrict the heart's ability to pump blood and become life-threatening.",
