    "longDesc": "Postmeningococcal arthritis",
    "plainEnglish": "Postmeningococcal arthritis is joint inflammation that develops as a complication after a meningococcal infection (a serious bacterial infection caused by Neisseria meningitidis). This condition occurs when the infection has cleared from the bloodstream and central nervous system, but the body's immune response causes joint swelling, pain, and stiffness, typically affecting the knees, wrists, and other large joints. It usually develops days to weeks after the acute meningococcal illness has been treated with antibiotics.",
