    "plainEnglish": "This code describes meningococcal infections caused by the bacterium Neisseria meningitidis that don't fit into the more common categories like meningitis or sepsis. These \"other\" infections might include meningococcal arthritis, eye infections, or localized infections in specific body parts. Symptoms vary depending on where the infection is but can range from joint pain and swelling to eye inflammation or other organ involvement.",
    "whoUses": "Infectious disease specialists, emergency medicine physicians, and hospitalists typically use this code when diagnosing and treating meningococcal infections that don't meet criteria for standard meningitis or bloodstream infection. This code appears in acute care settings (emergency department or hospital admission), and patients may see it on their EOB statement when hospitalized for a serious bacterial infection.",
