    "longDesc": "Meningococcal infection, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a confirmed bacterial infection caused by Neisseria meningitidis (meningococcus), but the doctor hasn't yet documented or determined which specific form or complication the infection has caused. The meningococcus bacterium can cause several serious illnesses, including meningitis (inflammation of brain/spinal cord membranes), septicemia (bloodstream infection), or other organ infections—all of which can develop rapidly and become life-threatening if not treated immediately with antibiotics.",
