    "plainEnglish": "Actinomycotic meningitis is a rare bacterial infection of the protective membranes surrounding the brain and spinal cord (the meninges) caused by bacteria called Actinomyces, usually from the mouth or jaw. This infection happens when the bacteria spread from an initial infection site—often a dental abscess or jaw bone infection—and reach the brain lining. Patients typically experience severe headache, high fever, stiff neck, and confusion, similar to other types of meningitis.",
