    "whoUses": "Infectious disease specialists and dermatologists commonly diagnose and treat cutaneous nocardiosis, often in office visits or outpatient clinics, though some patients may present to urgent care or the ER with severely infected wounds. This code appears on EOB statements when patients receive treatment for skin infections, particularly those requiring prolonged antibiotic therapy or wound management visits.",
