    "whoUses": "Infectious disease specialists, pulmonologists, and immunologists most commonly use this code when diagnosing and treating nocardiosis in hospitalized or critically ill patients, though it may also appear in primary care settings when referring patients for specialist evaluation. This code is less commonly seen on patient EOB statements due to the rarity of nocardiosis, but it would appear if a patient had laboratory-confirmed or clinically diagnosed nocardiosis requiring treatment and follow-up care.",
