    "shortDesc": "Secondary syphilitic female pelvic disease",
    "longDesc": "Secondary syphilitic female pelvic disease",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis describes a sexually transmitted infection (syphilis) that has progressed to the secondary stage and is now affecting a woman's reproductive organs and pelvis. In secondary syphilis, the infection has spread throughout the body after the initial infection site has healed, and in this case it's specifically causing inflammation in the uterus, fallopian tubes, ovaries, or surrounding pelvic tissues. Women with this condition may experience pelvic pain, abnormal vaginal discharge, painful intercourse, or irregular bleeding, along with other systemic symptoms like fever, rash, or swollen lymph nodes.",
