    "plainEnglish": "This code describes various skin rashes, sores, or other body manifestations that occur during the secondary stage of syphilis, a sexually transmitted infection caused by bacteria. Secondary syphilis happens weeks to months after the initial infection and can cause widespread symptoms like a rash (often on the palms and soles), mucous patches in the mouth, swollen lymph nodes, fever, and hair loss. These secondary symptoms indicate that the infection has spread throughout the body and requires immediate antibiotic treatment.",
