    "longDesc": "Early syphilis, latent",
    "plainEnglish": "Early latent syphilis means you have the syphilis infection in your body, but you have no visible symptoms or signs of the disease. This stage occurs within the first year after infection with the syphilis bacterium (Treponema pallidum), usually after the initial chancre sore has healed. You can still transmit the infection to others, especially through sexual contact or blood exposure, even though you feel completely healthy.",
    "whoUses": "This code is commonly used by infectious disease specialists, primary care physicians, urgent care centers, and STI clinics during routine screening or contact tracing investigations. It appears frequently in sexual health clinics, prenatal care settings, and blood bank facilities, and may appear on EOB statements when patients receive testing and treatment for syphilis.",
