    "longDesc": "Early syphilis, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Early syphilis, unspecified means you have been diagnosed with syphilis (a sexually transmitted infection caused by bacteria) in its early stages, but the specific form—whether it's the first stage (primary), second stage (secondary), or early latent stage—has not been documented or determined. Early syphilis can cause a painless sore at the infection site, a widespread rash, swollen lymph nodes, fever, or body aches, depending on the stage. Without treatment, syphilis can progress to serious complications affecting the heart, brain, and nervous system.",
    "whoUses": "This code is used by primary care physicians, infectious disease specialists, STI clinics, urgent care, and emergency departments when testing confirms syphilis but the clinical documentation doesn't specify which early stage is present. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients receiving serological testing, initial evaluation, or early antibiotic treatment for syphilis.",
