    "shortDesc": "Syphilitic endocarditis",
    "longDesc": "Syphilitic endocarditis",
    "plainEnglish": "Syphilitic endocarditis is a serious heart infection caused by untreated syphilis (a sexually transmitted infection caused by bacteria). The infection damages the inner lining of the heart chambers and valves, preventing the heart from pumping blood efficiently and potentially causing heart murmurs, leaks in the valves, and heart failure. This typically develops years after the initial syphilis infection if left untreated.",
    "whoUses": "Cardiologists, infectious disease specialists, and internists commonly use this code when diagnosing and treating late-stage syphilis complications, typically in hospital settings, cardiology clinics, or during cardiac workups. This code frequently appears on EOB statements for patients with untreated or inadequately treated syphilis presenting with cardiac symptoms requiring echocardiography, cardiac imaging, and antibiotic therapy.",
