    "plainEnglish": "Syphilitic cerebral arteritis occurs when the blood vessels in the brain become inflamed and damaged as a result of untreated or late-stage syphilis (a sexually transmitted bacterial infection). This inflammation can narrow or weaken the blood vessels in the brain, potentially leading to stroke, reduced blood flow to brain tissue, or other serious neurological complications. Patients may experience symptoms like headaches, dizziness, weakness, numbness, or neurological deficits depending on which blood vessels are affected.",
