    "plainEnglish": "This code refers to syphilis (a bacterial infection typically spread through sexual contact) that has spread to the brain and spinal fluid in ways other than the main recognized patterns. When untreated syphilis progresses, the bacteria can invade the nervous system and cause inflammation of the membranes surrounding the brain and spinal cord, leading to symptoms like headaches, confusion, stiff neck, or nerve problems. This is a serious condition that requires prompt antibiotic treatment to prevent permanent neurological damage.",
