    "plainEnglish": "Late syphilitic meningitis is an infection of the protective membranes surrounding the brain and spinal cord caused by untreated syphilis that has progressed over years or decades. Syphilis is a sexually transmitted infection caused by bacteria, and if left untreated, it can spread to the nervous system and cause inflammation of the meninges (the membranes covering the brain). This condition can cause severe headaches, neck stiffness, fever, and confusion, and requires urgent antibiotic treatment to prevent serious neurological damage or death.",
