    "plainEnglish": "Charcot's arthropathy in the context of tabes dorsalis is a severe, progressive joint condition caused by untreated or late-stage syphilis that damages the nerves controlling sensation and proprioception (body awareness). Because patients lose the ability to feel pain and know where their joints are in space, they repeatedly injure the joints without realizing it, leading to joint deterioration, swelling, instability, and sometimes complete joint destruction. This typically affects the knees, ankles, hips, or spine and develops over months to years.",
