    "plainEnglish": "This code refers to neurosyphilis—an advanced stage of untreated syphilis where the bacteria (Treponema pallidum) has spread to the nervous system and brain, causing various neurological symptoms. These symptoms can include confusion, memory problems, coordination difficulties, weakness, or nerve pain, depending on which parts of the nervous system are affected. It develops years after the initial syphilis infection goes untreated and can cause serious, sometimes permanent damage to the brain and spinal cord.",
    "whoUses": "Infectious disease specialists, neurologists, and primary care physicians commonly use this code when diagnosing or treating neurosyphilis, typically in outpatient clinics, hospitals, or during specialist consultations. This code frequently appears on EOBs for patients receiving antibiotic treatment (usually IV penicillin) and neurological evaluations, and may be documented following positive syphilis screening tests that indicate nervous system involvement.",
