    "whoUses": "Ophthalmologists, optometrists, pediatricians, and urgent care providers typically diagnose and treat this condition during office visits, emergency department visits, or newborn examinations in hospitals. This code commonly appears on EOB statements when patients seek treatment for eye infections, particularly in newborn care settings or sexually transmitted infection (STI) clinics.",
