    "whoUses": "Gynecologists, primary care physicians, and urgent care providers commonly diagnose and treat herpesviral cervicitis during pelvic exams or when evaluating vaginal symptoms. This code frequently appears on EOB statements for women seeking treatment for genital herpes complications, particularly during initial visits, follow-up appointments, or when antiviral medication is prescribed.",
