    "longDesc": "Meningitis due to Lyme disease",
    "plainEnglish": "Meningitis due to Lyme disease is a serious brain infection caused by the Lyme disease bacteria (Borrelia burgdorferi), which is spread through tick bites. The infection inflames the protective membranes surrounding the brain and spinal cord, causing severe headache, high fever, neck stiffness, sensitivity to light, and sometimes confusion or difficulty concentrating. This typically occurs weeks or months after an untreated or inadequately treated Lyme disease infection.",
    "whoUses": "Infectious disease specialists, neurologists, and emergency medicine physicians commonly diagnose and treat this condition in hospital or ER settings. This code may appear on EOB statements when patients require hospitalization, lumbar puncture testing, or specialized antibiotic treatment for Lyme meningitis.",
