    "whoUses": "Ophthalmologists, optometrists, and infectious disease specialists use this code, typically during eye clinic visits or evaluations in endemic regions. Primary care physicians in developing countries may also diagnose and treat active trachoma. This code occasionally appears on patient EOBs for eye care services but is less common in developed nations; it is more frequently documented in public health and international medicine settings.",
