    "plainEnglish": "This is a serious bacterial infection caused by a specific organism called Rickettsia tsutsugamushi, which is transmitted to humans through the bite of infected mites (also called chiggers) found in scrub vegetation, particularly in Asia and the Pacific region. The disease causes high fever, severe headache, muscle aches, and a characteristic skin rash, typically starting at the bite site and spreading across the body. Without treatment, this infection can damage vital organs and become life-threatening.",
