    "rawCode": "A801",
    "shortDesc": "Acute paralytic poliomyelitis, wild virus, imported",
    "longDesc": "Acute paralytic poliomyelitis, wild virus, imported",
    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis describes poliomyelitis (polio), a serious viral infection caused by the wild poliovirus that was acquired from outside the patient's home country. Polio attacks nerve cells in the spinal cord and brain, causing sudden paralysis (inability to move) in parts of the body, often starting in the legs and potentially spreading upward. The condition develops rapidly and can be life-threatening if it affects the muscles used for breathing.",
    "whoUses": "Infectious disease specialists, neurologists, and emergency medicine physicians use this code when diagnosing polio in patients with recent travel history or international exposure. This code appears in acute care settings such as hospitals and emergency departments, and typically on EOB statements for serious infectious disease consultations and hospitalizations, though polio is extremely rare in vaccinated populations.",
