    "longDesc": "Other acute paralytic poliomyelitis",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes poliomyelitis, a viral infection that damages the nerve cells controlling muscles, resulting in sudden weakness or paralysis. Unlike the most common form of polio (which affects the lower spine), this category covers less typical presentations of the disease. Symptoms develop rapidly and may include muscle weakness, pain, and paralysis in various parts of the body depending on which nerves are affected.",
    "whoUses": "Infectious disease specialists, neurologists, and emergency medicine physicians use this code when diagnosing a patient with acute polio presenting with paralysis in an atypical distribution. This code would appear in hospital settings or specialized clinics managing polio cases, and may be seen on EOB statements for hospitalized or intensive care patients, though polio is now extremely rare in developed countries due to vaccination programs.",
