    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a rare, fatal brain disease similar to the classic form of Creutzfeldt-Jakob disease (CJD), but of a different type or subtype. The disease causes progressive damage to brain tissue, leading to rapidly worsening problems with thinking, memory, coordination, and behavior, typically progressing from first symptoms to death within a year or two. Patients may experience personality changes, dementia, involuntary movements, and loss of bodily control as the disease advances.",
