    "plainEnglish": "Kuru is a rare, fatal brain disease caused by infectious proteins called prions that damage brain tissue, leading to progressive loss of muscle control, tremors, and severe dementia. The disease is spread through contaminated food or ritual practices and has an extremely long incubation period—sometimes 10-20 years before symptoms appear. Once symptoms develop, the condition steadily worsens until it becomes fatal, with no cure available.",
