    "plainEnglish": "Rabies is a severe viral infection that spreads through the saliva of infected animals, usually via bites or scratches, and attacks the nervous system. Once symptoms appear—such as fever, anxiety, confusion, hallucinations, difficulty swallowing, or aggressive behavior—rabies is almost always fatal without immediate treatment. This code indicates a confirmed case of rabies where the specific type or stage hasn't been specified in the medical record.",
