    "shortDesc": "Chikungunya virus disease",
    "longDesc": "Chikungunya virus disease",
    "plainEnglish": "Chikungunya is a viral infection spread by mosquitoes that causes fever, severe joint and muscle pain, and a rash. The virus gets its name from a Swahili word meaning \"that which bends up,\" referring to how the intense joint pain can make people stoop over. Most people recover within a few weeks, though some experience joint pain that can persist for months.",
    "whoUses": "Infectious disease specialists, emergency medicine physicians, and tropical medicine doctors use this code, particularly in patients returning from travel to endemic regions in Africa, Asia, and the Caribbean. It commonly appears on EOB statements for patients seeking care after international travel with fever and joint pain symptoms.",
