    "shortDesc": "O'nyong-nyong fever",
    "longDesc": "O'nyong-nyong fever",
    "plainEnglish": "O'nyong-nyong fever is a rare viral infection spread by mosquitoes, primarily found in Africa. It causes sudden onset of high fever, severe joint pain (especially in the hands, wrists, and ankles), muscle aches, and a rash that may appear on the trunk and limbs. The illness typically lasts a few days to a week, and while most people recover fully, some experience lingering joint pain for weeks or months afterward.",
