    "plainEnglish": "Venezuelan equine fever is a viral infection transmitted to humans through mosquito bites, primarily occurring in Central and South America. The infection causes sudden onset of fever, severe headaches, muscle aches, and joint pain that typically last several days; in some cases, it can progress to more serious neurological complications affecting the brain and spinal cord.",
