    "code": "A92.30",
    "rawCode": "A9230",
    "shortDesc": "West Nile virus infection, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "West Nile virus infection, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "West Nile virus infection is a disease spread by mosquito bites that affects your body's ability to function normally. Most people experience mild symptoms like fever, headache, body aches, and fatigue (similar to the flu), but some develop more serious complications affecting the brain or nervous system that can cause high fever, severe headaches, confusion, weakness, or even paralysis.",
