    "longDesc": "West Nile virus infection with other complications",
    "plainEnglish": "This code describes a West Nile virus infection that has progressed beyond the typical fever and body aches to cause additional serious health problems. West Nile virus is spread by infected mosquitoes and can affect the nervous system, joints, heart, or other organs, leading to complications like meningitis, severe fatigue, joint pain, or organ inflammation. These complications can develop weeks or months after the initial infection and may cause long-lasting symptoms.",
