    "plainEnglish": "Sandfly fever is a viral infection spread by tiny insects called sandflies, primarily found in warm, tropical regions around the Mediterranean Sea, Middle East, and parts of Africa and Asia. The infection causes sudden fever, severe headaches, muscle and joint pain, weakness, and sometimes a rash, typically lasting 2-4 days; it's rarely life-threatening but can cause significant discomfort and temporarily disable patients.",
