    "whoUses": "Emergency medicine physicians, infectious disease specialists, and primary care doctors diagnose and manage Colorado tick fever, particularly in patients with recent tick exposure in endemic areas. While not extremely common, this code appears on EOB statements for patients presenting with tick-borne illness in the western United States, especially during tick season (spring through fall).",
