    "plainEnglish": "This diagnosis means you have a fever caused by a virus that was transmitted to you through an insect bite, such as from a mosquito, tick, or other arthropod, but doctors haven't identified the specific virus responsible. Your body is mounting an immune response to the viral infection, causing elevated body temperature and often accompanying symptoms like body aches, fatigue, or headache. Without knowing the exact virus, treatment focuses on managing your symptoms while your immune system fights off the infection.",
